WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.551 --> 00:00:11.845
Stop. Claire Hale. Stop!

2
00:00:20.520 --> 00:00:22.313
<i>"I'd like to fry her eyeballs.</i>

3
00:00:22.397 --> 00:00:25.400
If no one else steps up
to kill the president. I will.

4
00:00:26.026 --> 00:00:27.027
I'd enjoy it."

5
00:00:27.861 --> 00:00:29.446
A tweet out of North Dakota.

6
00:00:29.738 --> 00:00:30.738
What else?

7
00:00:32.282 --> 00:00:35.160
"God never intended a woman
to rule this land.

8
00:00:35.243 --> 00:00:36.995
She is the anti-Christ.

9
00:00:37.829 --> 00:00:39.873
- And a Jew."
- A Jew?

10
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.751
- Do we really need to hear all of this?
- Yes.

11
00:00:43.877 --> 00:00:45.962
An unpublished editorial.

12
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:48.548
Someone pointing a gun at your likeness.

13
00:00:48.631 --> 00:00:51.426
Lots of other online stuff. including a...

14
00:00:52.677 --> 00:00:53.803
contest...

15
00:00:54.429 --> 00:00:55.429
For?

16
00:00:56.181 --> 00:00:58.224
For the most creative way to kill you.

17
00:00:59.434 --> 00:01:00.435
And the winner?

18
00:01:01.519 --> 00:01:02.645
Rather not say. ma'am.

19
00:01:03.772 --> 00:01:06.649
I want to hear.
Just hand me the report. Rick.

20
00:01:09.402 --> 00:01:11.488
It involves. essentially. skinning you.

21
00:01:12.822 --> 00:01:14.824
Cutting your body into dozens of pieces

22
00:01:14.908 --> 00:01:17.118
and arranging them
in the shape of the American flag.

23
00:01:19.913 --> 00:01:22.665
Flesh for the white stripes.
blood for the red.

24
00:01:24.959 --> 00:01:25.959
What else?

25
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:29.756
Lot of threats
involving the C-word. ma'am.

26
00:01:29.839 --> 00:01:31.966
Lots and lots of the C-word.
unfortunately.

27
00:01:34.010 --> 00:01:35.370
You mean Claire? It's a long list.

28
00:01:37.639 --> 00:01:40.850
- If you really want me to. I'll...
- Listen. I am not the first president

29
00:01:40.934 --> 00:01:41.976
to face threats.

30
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:44.646
I know with Francis.
sometimes there were several a day.

31
00:01:44.729 --> 00:01:45.939
Is it about the same

32
00:01:46.397 --> 00:01:47.857
what we're dealing with here?

33
00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:50.276
It's...

34
00:01:50.485 --> 00:01:51.903
significantly up.

35
00:01:51.986 --> 00:01:52.821
By how much?

36
00:01:52.904 --> 00:01:54.948
There are roughly
four times as many threats

37
00:01:55.031 --> 00:01:56.950
on any given day since you took office.

38
00:01:57.033 --> 00:01:59.577
Now it's twice that since Francis died.

39
00:02:01.538 --> 00:02:03.581
I thought everyone loves a widow.

40
00:02:03.665 --> 00:02:06.084
Not if she's also
Commander-in-Chief. I guess.

41
00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:08.216
These are not rational people.
Madam President.

42
00:02:08.253 --> 00:02:10.839
But. ma'am. as far as today's threat.

43
00:02:10.922 --> 00:02:12.608
regarding your first
scheduled appearance...

44
00:02:12.632 --> 00:02:14.092
We're canceling the appearance.

45
00:02:16.427 --> 00:02:17.804
We're not canceling.

46
00:02:18.847 --> 00:02:19.889
It's a military base.

47
00:02:19.973 --> 00:02:22.517
That's got to be the safest place on Earth
for a president.

48
00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:25.353
An anonymous soldier
has made a serious threat...

49
00:02:25.436 --> 00:02:28.231
"To shoot me in the cunt on behalf
of the United States of America."

50
00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:30.400
Yes. Mark. I heard.
The threat's unconfirmed.

51
00:02:30.483 --> 00:02:32.203
He says he's among
those shipping out today.

52
00:02:32.235 --> 00:02:34.296
- Anyone can claim that.
- And that you have no right

53
00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:36.698
waging war in Syria. You. in particular.

54
00:02:36.781 --> 00:02:38.867
I think we stay away.
Rick. don't you agree?

55
00:02:38.950 --> 00:02:41.494
There's no proof the threat is credible.
Isn't that right. Rick?

56
00:02:41.578 --> 00:02:43.705
Our intelligence division
is investigating.

57
00:02:43.788 --> 00:02:46.624
and the advance team is already there.
but it'll take at least a day

58
00:02:46.708 --> 00:02:48.334
to comb through that base.

59
00:02:48.418 --> 00:02:51.462
I think what the vice president says
is the best course.

60
00:02:51.546 --> 00:02:55.091
- Maybe by tomorrow you could...
- Tomorrow is the fifth of July.

61
00:02:56.926 --> 00:02:59.512
- Yes. ma'am.
- So what do you suggest I do?

62
00:02:59.596 --> 00:03:03.057
- Wish the nation a happy belated birthday?
- Our only concern is your safety...

63
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:04.434
We're not cancelling.

64
00:03:05.143 --> 00:03:07.687
I am sending those soldiers
onto a battlefield.

65
00:03:08.688 --> 00:03:10.815
The first female president
of the United States

66
00:03:10.899 --> 00:03:14.027
is not gonna keep her mouth shut
on the Fourth of fucking July.

67
00:04:54.377 --> 00:04:56.462
Lieutenant General Gallagher
would understand.

68
00:04:57.046 --> 00:05:00.008
- I could appear instead. Speak for you.
- Stop.

69
00:05:03.761 --> 00:05:06.431
Is it my safety that concerns you.

70
00:05:06.514 --> 00:05:08.725
or my potential endorsement of Gallagher?

71
00:05:08.808 --> 00:05:10.435
Your safety first. of course.

72
00:05:10.977 --> 00:05:13.563
But singling her out.
that's a provocation.

73
00:05:13.646 --> 00:05:14.897
And so?

74
00:05:15.523 --> 00:05:16.941
I can't provoke them?

75
00:05:17.025 --> 00:05:19.444
You're forwarding a candidate
the Shepherds are against.

76
00:05:19.527 --> 00:05:20.820
in their home state.

77
00:05:21.612 --> 00:05:24.699
- After months of negotiation.
- This is not a negotiation.

78
00:05:24.782 --> 00:05:27.327
this is an ultimatum.
Sign the bill or what?

79
00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:28.786
Or what. Mark?

80
00:05:32.123 --> 00:05:34.584
When Francis was looking
to finance his foundation.

81
00:05:34.667 --> 00:05:37.170
why did you point him
towards Bill and Annette?

82
00:05:37.253 --> 00:05:39.422
I didn't. Raymond Tusk arranged it.

83
00:05:39.505 --> 00:05:41.215
Or maybe they reached out to him?

84
00:05:42.425 --> 00:05:43.551
I don't remember.

85
00:05:44.218 --> 00:05:47.180
I... What does it matter?
They're working with you now.

86
00:05:48.973 --> 00:05:51.476
I need to meet
with the Shepherds directly.

87
00:05:51.559 --> 00:05:52.435
Madam President.

88
00:05:52.518 --> 00:05:54.437
I'll see them before my appearance
at the base.

89
00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:55.897
- You can't.
- I what?

90
00:05:58.274 --> 00:05:59.942
I'll let them know.

91
00:06:01.527 --> 00:06:02.527
Thank you.

92
00:06:07.784 --> 00:06:11.621
You're due at the base by 4:45.
which will have you back here by 8:30.

93
00:06:11.913 --> 00:06:14.123
The fireworks show
begins right after nine.

94
00:06:14.207 --> 00:06:18.086
And the <i>Examiner</i> would love your okay
on the photos.

95
00:06:33.434 --> 00:06:36.062
Is there any progress
on the source of the sound?

96
00:06:36.145 --> 00:06:37.897
The GSA is still looking into it.

97
00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:40.584
They're checking the floorboards
above and below. in case there's...

98
00:06:40.608 --> 00:06:42.318
I don't want to wait anymore.

99
00:06:42.819 --> 00:06:44.362
Please tell the executive housekeeper

100
00:06:44.445 --> 00:06:46.906
I'd like the former president's belongings
packed up.

101
00:06:46.989 --> 00:06:48.366
I'll have it taken care of.

102
00:09:05.628 --> 00:09:08.381
It's not true what he told you
all those years ago.

103
00:09:09.340 --> 00:09:12.468
That there are two kinds.
useful and useless.

104
00:09:13.261 --> 00:09:14.679
There's only one kind.

105
00:09:15.471 --> 00:09:17.306
Pain is pain.

106
00:09:27.149 --> 00:09:28.192
Francis...

107
00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:31.195
I'm done with you.

108
00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:44.040
There.

109
00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:45.585
No more pain.

110
00:09:54.218 --> 00:09:55.845
You do this all day?

111
00:09:58.431 --> 00:10:01.851
I'm under psychiatric observation. Seth.
This is what you do.

112
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:07.857
Who's your new tailor?

113
00:10:09.317 --> 00:10:10.526
You gotta look the part.

114
00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:14.155
So. when do they decide

115
00:10:14.739 --> 00:10:16.115
whether you're crazy or not?

116
00:10:17.366 --> 00:10:18.659
Because if you're not.

117
00:10:19.285 --> 00:10:20.703
you should come work for us.

118
00:10:21.537 --> 00:10:22.537
Us?

119
00:10:24.707 --> 00:10:26.834
Have you been working there
for about five minutes?

120
00:10:26.959 --> 00:10:28.252
It's been a month. actually.

121
00:10:30.671 --> 00:10:32.298
So his body wasn't even cold.

122
00:10:32.632 --> 00:10:33.872
It's what he would have wanted.

123
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.069
The Underwood Foundation
was basically gonna be modeled

124
00:10:36.093 --> 00:10:37.613
after the Shepherd Freedom Foundation.

125
00:10:38.054 --> 00:10:39.347
I don't need the job.

126
00:10:39.889 --> 00:10:44.018
Oh. Well. for a confessed murderer.
you're pretty confident.

127
00:10:44.935 --> 00:10:46.354
I'm about to be pardoned.

128
00:10:46.896 --> 00:10:47.896
Pardon?

129
00:10:49.398 --> 00:10:51.238
You really think
that she's gonna give you one?

130
00:10:51.275 --> 00:10:54.570
As usual. you don't know
what the fuck you're talking about.

131
00:10:54.987 --> 00:10:57.865
You know. there wasn't the kind of crowd
that you'd expect for him

132
00:10:57.948 --> 00:10:59.075
down there in Gaffney.

133
00:10:59.158 --> 00:11:00.701
He wanted to be buried in Arlington.

134
00:11:01.494 --> 00:11:02.828
Not next to his father.

135
00:11:02.912 --> 00:11:04.413
That's not what his wife said.

136
00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:09.710
Tell me something.

137
00:11:11.212 --> 00:11:12.630
She even shed a tear?

138
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:14.674
You know...

139
00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:17.843
I'm almost envious. to tell you the truth.

140
00:11:19.261 --> 00:11:21.138
That even beyond the grave.

141
00:11:22.014 --> 00:11:24.141
you'd do anything for Francis Underwood.

142
00:11:29.980 --> 00:11:32.191
Doug. do you have my lighter?

143
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:39.657
Much obliged.

144
00:11:45.246 --> 00:11:46.580
Was that who I thought it was?

145
00:11:47.123 --> 00:11:49.625
Fred Amburg? He went off the deep end?

146
00:11:50.042 --> 00:11:51.627
Everyone has problems. Seth.

147
00:11:52.712 --> 00:11:54.463
Especially the ones who think they don't.

148
00:12:12.857 --> 00:12:14.650
- Claire.
- Annette.

149
00:12:15.651 --> 00:12:17.945
Oh. did you get my note?

150
00:12:18.112 --> 00:12:21.115
Oh. I haven't had the courage
to read the condolences yet.

151
00:12:22.116 --> 00:12:25.244
It's good to see you finally out
and about.

152
00:12:25.619 --> 00:12:27.288
Oh. what you've been through.

153
00:12:29.331 --> 00:12:30.791
You know all about it.

154
00:12:31.375 --> 00:12:34.503
Well. for a long time.
I pretended he was still alive.

155
00:12:35.337 --> 00:12:36.756
Out of town.

156
00:12:36.839 --> 00:12:39.049
It was our son Duncan
that really saved me.

157
00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:42.553
Of course. we weren't married
anywhere near as long as you and Frank.

158
00:12:43.220 --> 00:12:44.220
Claire Hale.

159
00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:46.807
Nine years.

160
00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:49.059
Late spring.

161
00:12:49.935 --> 00:12:51.103
Sun Valley.

162
00:12:54.315 --> 00:12:55.816
You look exactly the same.

163
00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:58.027
Well. it's cities that age you.

164
00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.029
it's what I tell everyone.

165
00:13:02.323 --> 00:13:06.118
I hope you don't mind saying hello
to a few of our closest friends.

166
00:13:07.369 --> 00:13:10.247
They're just here for a cocktail
before the...

167
00:13:10.331 --> 00:13:13.292
the sun goes down
and the rest of the party shows up.

168
00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:16.962
My sister's fireworks show have become
a bit of a tradition.

169
00:13:20.841 --> 00:13:23.511
Don't worry. They know how to be discreet.

170
00:13:28.849 --> 00:13:31.769
Scotty here just got his hands
on Nexis Security.

171
00:13:31.852 --> 00:13:34.230
I heard you are speaking
to the vice president about this.

172
00:13:34.313 --> 00:13:36.023
It's a company of peacekeepers. mostly.

173
00:13:36.106 --> 00:13:39.318
Oh. tremendous potential
to create global partnerships.

174
00:13:39.401 --> 00:13:42.530
Your husband helped me secure the deal.
I wanted to bring him onto the Board.

175
00:13:43.447 --> 00:13:44.448
Bill was saying...

176
00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:46.033
Yes. I was just saying.

177
00:13:46.116 --> 00:13:50.704
Why in the world do they play
the "1812 Overture" at a fireworks show?

178
00:13:50.996 --> 00:13:53.541
It's Russian. for Chrissakes.
in every sense.

179
00:13:54.625 --> 00:13:56.293
This is Tabitha.

180
00:13:56.544 --> 00:13:58.128
Oh. Peters. I know.

181
00:13:59.338 --> 00:14:00.338
Frank...

182
00:14:01.006 --> 00:14:03.551
- Wasn't he planning to be here today?
- He was.

183
00:14:03.634 --> 00:14:05.344
You must miss him terribly.

184
00:14:06.428 --> 00:14:09.139
I had some long
and hard-fought conversations with him.

185
00:14:09.223 --> 00:14:12.726
He was going to help me resolve this
AFL-CIO thing

186
00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:14.770
that's been going on forever
out in Nevada.

187
00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:16.605
with your help. of course.

188
00:14:16.689 --> 00:14:19.275
When the union stands
in the way of innovation.

189
00:14:19.358 --> 00:14:21.277
it's sentencing itself to death.

190
00:14:22.611 --> 00:14:25.322
I do admire the way you hang on
to your party.

191
00:14:25.406 --> 00:14:26.699
Your loyalty.

192
00:14:28.033 --> 00:14:30.327
Did I hear that
Lieutenant General Nancy Gallagher

193
00:14:30.411 --> 00:14:32.246
will be appearing with you later today?

194
00:14:36.333 --> 00:14:38.460
I think she'd make an excellent candidate.

195
00:14:38.544 --> 00:14:40.921
if she decides to run. of course.

196
00:14:41.005 --> 00:14:43.173
Oh. she's going to run.

197
00:14:48.095 --> 00:14:50.598
The president is on a tight schedule.

198
00:14:58.022 --> 00:14:59.023
Excuse me.

199
00:15:16.123 --> 00:15:18.000
Well. this is a surprise.

200
00:15:19.627 --> 00:15:21.921
You know how Midwesterners
feel about those.

201
00:15:22.004 --> 00:15:25.132
Oh. don't listen to him.
It's about time you came out.

202
00:15:25.591 --> 00:15:27.635
Seems we have some things to discuss.

203
00:15:27.968 --> 00:15:28.886
Yeah.

204
00:15:28.969 --> 00:15:32.222
Well. as far as this special election
is concerned. Claire.

205
00:15:32.306 --> 00:15:35.517
you need to know that
the soon-to-be-retiring Miss Gallagher

206
00:15:36.393 --> 00:15:37.645
is out of question.

207
00:15:38.145 --> 00:15:42.650
And I'm happy to see we're both fans
of the Declaration of Independence.

208
00:15:42.733 --> 00:15:44.318
unalienable rights and all that.

209
00:15:44.401 --> 00:15:46.904
But it says down here in the speech
you're gonna give later...

210
00:15:46.987 --> 00:15:48.822
Miss Gallagher has my support.

211
00:15:50.824 --> 00:15:52.660
I believe Mark conveyed our concerns.

212
00:15:53.077 --> 00:15:54.828
And communicated mine. I hope.

213
00:15:55.579 --> 00:15:58.666
She's a tax and spend Democrat
underneath that uniform.

214
00:15:58.749 --> 00:16:01.377
- A patriot with a pristine resume.
- Claire.

215
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:04.296
Who is very vocal about keeping
private contractors away

216
00:16:04.380 --> 00:16:06.775
- from US military operations.
- Even as a negotiating point.

217
00:16:06.799 --> 00:16:07.879
you can do better than her.

218
00:16:07.925 --> 00:16:10.094
And I am tired of these delays.
Madam President.

219
00:16:10.177 --> 00:16:11.595
It is time for you to deliver.

220
00:16:15.015 --> 00:16:17.559
- Your husband and I had an agreement.
- Francis is dead.

221
00:16:17.643 --> 00:16:19.937
- Promises were made.
- Not by me.

222
00:16:22.147 --> 00:16:26.026
Just like you. I like to negotiate
my own agreements.

223
00:16:26.527 --> 00:16:29.613
And make no mistake about it.
the lieutenant general is not an anomaly.

224
00:16:29.697 --> 00:16:32.741
I know that. I've seen your list
of candidates for the midterms...

225
00:16:32.825 --> 00:16:35.911
- Yes. mostly women.
- I don't care what sex they are.

226
00:16:35.995 --> 00:16:38.622
And for the record.
nobody loves women more than me.

227
00:16:38.706 --> 00:16:41.083
But this slate of yours.
it will bankrupt the country.

228
00:16:41.166 --> 00:16:44.044
They will set us back a generation.
They will completely...

229
00:16:44.128 --> 00:16:47.297
Support me and what I stand for.

230
00:16:47.673 --> 00:16:48.590
And what is that?

231
00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:50.342
- Oh. come on. Bill.
- No. no. Tell me.

232
00:16:50.426 --> 00:16:52.011
I wanna know. What's your mission?

233
00:16:52.094 --> 00:16:54.263
- I wanna know what your platform is.
- Oh. please.

234
00:16:54.346 --> 00:16:56.557
I know you'd like
to drown DC all at once.

235
00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:59.101
But I'm gonna tell you right now.
I cannot let that happen.

236
00:16:59.184 --> 00:17:01.562
I still believe in government
and its ability

237
00:17:01.645 --> 00:17:04.398
to make the everyday lives
of its citizens better.

238
00:17:04.481 --> 00:17:06.442
- Yeah.
- You don't wanna support my slate.

239
00:17:06.525 --> 00:17:07.525
that's fine.

240
00:17:08.193 --> 00:17:11.155
- Claire...
- All I ask is stay out of the way.

241
00:17:14.491 --> 00:17:16.535
There's a bill sitting on your desk.

242
00:17:18.162 --> 00:17:20.122
A bill that took years...

243
00:17:20.581 --> 00:17:23.208
and money to get passed.

244
00:17:23.459 --> 00:17:24.793
You sign that.

245
00:17:25.544 --> 00:17:27.838
and I know I got a friend
in the White House.

246
00:17:29.381 --> 00:17:30.549
If not...

247
00:17:32.301 --> 00:17:33.886
- Then I don't.
- Enough.

248
00:17:37.056 --> 00:17:39.391
Nothing good happens to you
when she's around.

249
00:17:39.475 --> 00:17:40.476
Nothing.

250
00:17:41.435 --> 00:17:43.145
Why did you come out for Francis?

251
00:17:43.812 --> 00:17:45.105
For his foundation?

252
00:17:45.189 --> 00:17:47.232
I don't think you ever really liked him.

253
00:17:48.317 --> 00:17:51.695
Probably never respected him.
Why back him now?

254
00:17:53.572 --> 00:17:55.199
Because he gave us you.

255
00:17:58.911 --> 00:18:01.747
Tell our friends I'll be back down
in time for the fireworks.

256
00:18:10.297 --> 00:18:13.342
Just so you know. I always liked Frank.

257
00:18:15.677 --> 00:18:17.137
His desperation.

258
00:18:21.266 --> 00:18:23.060
I'm sorry you can't stay.

259
00:18:23.685 --> 00:18:26.146
I do enjoy curating our little show.

260
00:18:27.356 --> 00:18:30.275
I collect a variety of fireworks shells
as I travel.

261
00:18:30.859 --> 00:18:32.653
Italy. Spain. China.

262
00:18:34.446 --> 00:18:36.949
Do you know what the hardest color
to make is?

263
00:18:39.201 --> 00:18:41.328
- Red?
- No. red's easy.

264
00:18:41.745 --> 00:18:42.955
White's easy.

265
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:45.249
It's blue.

266
00:18:45.582 --> 00:18:48.418
Very tricky chemistry
involving copper and heat.

267
00:18:48.836 --> 00:18:51.463
A truly bright blue is extremely elusive.

268
00:18:53.757 --> 00:18:56.468
Whatever Francis promised or did...

269
00:18:57.594 --> 00:18:59.054
is buried with him.

270
00:18:59.930 --> 00:19:01.223
No. I know.

271
00:19:02.891 --> 00:19:04.977
We all need to let him go.

272
00:19:05.894 --> 00:19:08.230
Start from some kind of scratch.

273
00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:12.276
Though it must haunt you.

274
00:19:13.652 --> 00:19:15.821
the fact that he died next to you in bed.

275
00:19:23.495 --> 00:19:24.496
Hon...

276
00:19:27.207 --> 00:19:28.250
be patient.

277
00:19:33.213 --> 00:19:35.900
- She doesn't like the name?
- I think she finds it incomplete.

278
00:19:35.924 --> 00:19:37.569
What's wrong with
the Comprehensive Safety Act?

279
00:19:37.593 --> 00:19:39.112
Comprehensive Chemical Safety Act?

280
00:19:39.136 --> 00:19:41.030
Or we could go back
to the Smarter Safety Act.

281
00:19:41.054 --> 00:19:44.057
- Would she like "Smarter" better?
- No. we need a good acronym.

282
00:19:44.141 --> 00:19:46.268
Mr. Vice President? Mark?

283
00:19:48.729 --> 00:19:49.729
Yeah. Agreed.

284
00:19:50.189 --> 00:19:53.901
At one point. we talked about
the Repeal Unsafe Regulation Act.

285
00:19:53.984 --> 00:19:55.736
That's RURAL if we come up with an L.

286
00:19:55.819 --> 00:19:56.737
Legislation?

287
00:19:56.820 --> 00:19:58.464
That doesn't make sense
with the rest of it.

288
00:19:58.488 --> 00:20:00.741
"RURAL" is too hard to say.
"SAFE" is good.

289
00:20:00.824 --> 00:20:02.409
Safety. Future.

290
00:20:02.492 --> 00:20:06.705
- I like "FUTURE."
- Federal Universal Toxic and Unsafe...

291
00:20:07.122 --> 00:20:09.041
- Regulation Eradication.
- Okay.

292
00:20:09.666 --> 00:20:11.793
- The FUTURE Act.
- That could work.

293
00:20:12.377 --> 00:20:16.632
May I ask. Mr. Vice President.
does her hesitation go beyond the name?

294
00:20:18.300 --> 00:20:20.427
She'll come around. I'm guessing...

295
00:20:21.637 --> 00:20:23.198
by the end of the day.

296
00:20:23.222 --> 00:20:24.765
Because in one form or another.

297
00:20:24.848 --> 00:20:27.448
- this bill has been on her desk since...
- She'll sign it. Henry.

298
00:20:28.477 --> 00:20:30.062
Bill.

299
00:20:34.233 --> 00:20:35.400
What do you want me to do?

300
00:20:35.484 --> 00:20:37.444
Yank her from her own military base?

301
00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:45.702
When. in the course of human events.
it becomes necessary

302
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:48.538
for one people
to dissolve the political bands

303
00:20:48.622 --> 00:20:50.249
which have connected them with another.

304
00:20:50.707 --> 00:20:52.542
you just have to do it.

305
00:20:53.252 --> 00:20:55.003
Sever the relationship.

306
00:20:56.088 --> 00:20:58.340
Our nation's founding document.

307
00:20:58.423 --> 00:21:00.425
the Declaration of Independence...

308
00:21:00.509 --> 00:21:01.927
America's independence...

309
00:21:02.010 --> 00:21:04.721
was hard-fought and hard-won.

310
00:21:05.430 --> 00:21:06.556
Are you still there?

311
00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:10.727
Our Founding Fathers
imagined a nation that was free.

312
00:21:11.436 --> 00:21:12.980
Free from despotism.

313
00:21:13.522 --> 00:21:15.565
Free from absolute tyranny.

314
00:21:16.108 --> 00:21:18.318
Free from an oppressive king.

315
00:21:18.735 --> 00:21:19.903
Do you miss Francis?

316
00:21:19.987 --> 00:21:21.989
Tyrants come in many forms.

317
00:21:23.073 --> 00:21:27.536
From the American oligarchs trying
to change the very fabric of our society.

318
00:21:28.537 --> 00:21:30.998
to autocrats threatening from abroad.

319
00:21:32.165 --> 00:21:36.795
Now. each one of us
has to defend our destiny.

320
00:21:37.838 --> 00:21:39.256
And as I see it.

321
00:21:39.339 --> 00:21:43.969
the fight against tyranny
is the only justification for war.

322
00:21:45.512 --> 00:21:49.683
My first 100 days as president
have been difficult.

323
00:21:51.018 --> 00:21:52.477
I lost my husband.

324
00:21:53.687 --> 00:21:56.315
We were about
to celebrate 30 years together.

325
00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:59.318
But I know what he would want.

326
00:21:59.818 --> 00:22:02.696
For me to stop mourning and carry on.

327
00:22:03.780 --> 00:22:07.034
With the help of women like
Lieutenant General Nancy Gallagher.

328
00:22:07.117 --> 00:22:09.494
my presidency will not rest.

329
00:22:10.162 --> 00:22:12.414
Nancy has been an inspiration to me.

330
00:22:12.956 --> 00:22:14.750
A tireless warrior.

331
00:22:14.833 --> 00:22:18.795
I promise her and all of you
that I will work on behalf of the rights

332
00:22:18.879 --> 00:22:22.758
and freedoms earned over the last
241 years of our democracy.

333
00:22:24.801 --> 00:22:26.553
As I look into the eyes

334
00:22:26.636 --> 00:22:29.348
of you brave soldiers
standing before me today...

335
00:22:29.431 --> 00:22:30.349
Here's the thing.

336
00:22:30.432 --> 00:22:32.476
I'm feeling so proud right now.

337
00:22:33.018 --> 00:22:34.936
Proud to be your Commander-in-Chief.

338
00:22:35.228 --> 00:22:37.814
Whatever Francis told you
the last five years.

339
00:22:37.898 --> 00:22:39.274
don't believe a word of it.

340
00:22:39.358 --> 00:22:42.569
Our country is 241 years old. my friends.

341
00:22:43.195 --> 00:22:45.655
Let's wish this great nation
a happy birthday.

342
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:46.948
Say it with me.

343
00:22:47.032 --> 00:22:49.368
Happy birthday. America!

344
00:22:49.451 --> 00:22:52.204
Happy Birthday. America!

345
00:22:52.287 --> 00:22:53.806
It's going to be different for you and me.

346
00:22:53.830 --> 00:22:54.915
<i>One more time.</i>

347
00:22:54.998 --> 00:22:56.291
I'm going to tell you the truth.

348
00:22:56.375 --> 00:22:58.835
Happy Birthday. America.

349
00:23:00.337 --> 00:23:01.977
- Thank you for your service.
- Thank you.

350
00:23:03.006 --> 00:23:04.466
Thank you for your service.

351
00:23:05.550 --> 00:23:07.469
- Thank you for your service.
- Thank you.

352
00:23:09.346 --> 00:23:12.349
I want you to know how wonderful it is
to be here and meet

353
00:23:12.432 --> 00:23:14.017
all of you new recruits.

354
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:15.310
So. thank you.

355
00:23:15.644 --> 00:23:16.937
Thank you for your service.

356
00:23:17.020 --> 00:23:18.605
- Thank you.
- Thank you. ma'am.

357
00:23:18.939 --> 00:23:21.441
Thank you for your service.
Where are you from. private?

358
00:23:21.525 --> 00:23:23.026
Kalamazoo. Mr. President.

359
00:23:24.152 --> 00:23:26.312
- Excuse me. Madam President.
- That's quite all right.

360
00:23:26.655 --> 00:23:28.198
I actually hate "Madam."

361
00:23:28.281 --> 00:23:30.742
Makes me sound like I'm running a brothel
and not a country.

362
00:23:30.826 --> 00:23:33.471
- Thank you for your service.
- Thank you. Madam President.

363
00:23:33.495 --> 00:23:35.038
Thank you for your service.

364
00:23:35.122 --> 00:23:36.790
And where are you from. Pvt. Burton?

365
00:23:36.873 --> 00:23:38.125
South Bend. ma'am.

366
00:23:38.208 --> 00:23:40.085
Oh. I love Indiana.

367
00:23:40.502 --> 00:23:42.504
I enlisted right before you took office.

368
00:23:42.587 --> 00:23:45.507
Well. I promise you
and every woman in this country

369
00:23:45.590 --> 00:23:47.008
that during my presidency

370
00:23:47.092 --> 00:23:49.386
the key components
of the Equal Rights Amendment

371
00:23:49.845 --> 00:23:51.388
will finally pass.

372
00:23:51.471 --> 00:23:53.098
I'm going to make sure of it.

373
00:23:53.807 --> 00:23:55.600
I want you to know I support you.

374
00:23:56.601 --> 00:23:58.270
Do you even have a plan?

375
00:23:59.187 --> 00:24:00.230
What did you say?

376
00:24:01.815 --> 00:24:03.817
One that won't get us all killed?

377
00:24:04.234 --> 00:24:05.485
Oh. man...

378
00:24:06.778 --> 00:24:09.072
Would you have asked me that
if I were a man?

379
00:24:18.707 --> 00:24:19.791
Madam President!

380
00:24:21.126 --> 00:24:24.212
One question. please!

381
00:25:33.907 --> 00:25:36.993
How much longer till we get to the plane?

382
00:25:37.077 --> 00:25:39.579
Just another 25 minutes or so.
Madam President.

383
00:25:39.913 --> 00:25:41.623
Okay. thank you.

384
00:25:41.706 --> 00:25:43.041
Shit!

385
00:25:44.459 --> 00:25:46.499
- Is she shot?
- Stay down. stay down!

386
00:25:46.920 --> 00:25:48.964
Shots fired! Shots fired!

387
00:25:49.047 --> 00:25:51.328
Are you okay. Madam President?
- Are you all right? - Yes.

388
00:25:53.093 --> 00:25:54.302
Lone Star is safe.

389
00:26:16.366 --> 00:26:19.127
Sir. someone
just tried to kill the president.

390
00:26:23.039 --> 00:26:24.708
I just got the alert. Is she all right?

391
00:26:25.250 --> 00:26:26.250
This way.

392
00:26:42.517 --> 00:26:43.560
Lincoln.

393
00:26:45.061 --> 00:26:48.481
Garfield. McKinley. Kennedy.

394
00:26:49.816 --> 00:26:52.193
Successful assassinations. total of four.

395
00:26:56.239 --> 00:26:58.908
The attempts... Nine?

396
00:27:00.243 --> 00:27:03.246
Jackson. both Roosevelts.

397
00:27:04.706 --> 00:27:06.750
Truman. Ford twice.

398
00:27:07.459 --> 00:27:08.501
Reagan...

399
00:27:09.919 --> 00:27:12.005
the first Underwood and...

400
00:27:14.507 --> 00:27:17.510
I will say. whoever tried to kill me.

401
00:27:18.303 --> 00:27:23.099
perversely. it's the first sign
of real respect I've gotten in 100 days.

402
00:27:33.026 --> 00:27:34.444
Somebody tried to kill her.

403
00:27:36.738 --> 00:27:37.738
Bill.

404
00:27:40.325 --> 00:27:41.493
Can you blame them?

405
00:27:43.703 --> 00:27:45.955
The Underwoods
have always been hard of hearing.

406
00:27:47.040 --> 00:27:48.750
She's not him.

407
00:27:48.833 --> 00:27:50.251
No. no.

408
00:27:50.335 --> 00:27:51.586
She is not.

409
00:27:51.878 --> 00:27:53.963
<i>You </i>know that better than anyone.

410
00:27:56.341 --> 00:27:57.634
Is it public?

411
00:27:58.385 --> 00:28:01.471
Secret Service shut it down.
Standard procedure. apparently.

412
00:28:01.554 --> 00:28:03.848
Threats beget threats.

413
00:28:05.433 --> 00:28:06.433
Bill...

414
00:28:07.352 --> 00:28:08.853
were you behind this?

415
00:28:12.399 --> 00:28:13.650
We're gonna miss the show.

416
00:28:22.367 --> 00:28:24.619
- How are y'all?
- Madam President.

417
00:28:24.703 --> 00:28:25.703
Hi. I'm so sorry.

418
00:28:25.745 --> 00:28:27.580
I want to apologize
for the late departure.

419
00:28:27.664 --> 00:28:30.667
I know you all have families
and festivities waiting.

420
00:28:30.750 --> 00:28:34.087
Madam President.
may I ask what happened?

421
00:28:34.379 --> 00:28:39.050
Oh. the Beast was re-routed due
to security concerns. Pretty routine.

422
00:28:39.551 --> 00:28:43.138
I know it's been a while
since I've been back here.

423
00:28:43.221 --> 00:28:45.849
I just wanted to wish you all
a very happy Fourth.

424
00:28:45.932 --> 00:28:49.602
even if you're gonna be celebrating it
on the fifth. I'm so sorry.

425
00:28:49.686 --> 00:28:52.188
Your speech. afterwards with...

426
00:28:52.272 --> 00:28:54.023
Yes. the new recruit.

427
00:28:54.941 --> 00:28:58.486
If a new recruit. especially a female one.
can't speak her mind.

428
00:28:58.570 --> 00:29:01.781
I don't know what kind of country
we actually are.

429
00:29:05.910 --> 00:29:07.954
And be sure to tell us
if you run out of beer.

430
00:29:08.037 --> 00:29:10.248
Because I am sure
there's a couple of cases left over

431
00:29:10.331 --> 00:29:12.876
from the Carter administration.

432
00:29:13.710 --> 00:29:14.878
And you're new.

433
00:29:16.212 --> 00:29:19.299
Yes. ma'am. Melody Cruz.
I'm with Beltway Television.

434
00:29:19.799 --> 00:29:21.885
Well. I hope everyone
is making you feel at home.

435
00:29:22.343 --> 00:29:23.261
Very much so.

436
00:29:23.344 --> 00:29:25.096
It's an honor to finally meet you.

437
00:29:25.638 --> 00:29:26.973
I'm a bit overwhelmed. sorry.

438
00:29:27.056 --> 00:29:29.726
- Don't worry. I don't bite.
- No. I know.

439
00:29:31.144 --> 00:29:34.773
It's strange. I was supposed
to interview your husband.

440
00:29:35.732 --> 00:29:37.984
It was scheduled for a few days
after he died.

441
00:29:39.152 --> 00:29:42.655
It was going to be an exclusive.
We'd had a number of pre-interviews.

442
00:29:42.989 --> 00:29:44.657
Questions we'd agreed on.

443
00:29:46.201 --> 00:29:47.285
Questions like?

444
00:29:48.870 --> 00:29:51.790
Like. was the president
going to pardon him?

445
00:29:52.707 --> 00:29:53.750
And when?

446
00:29:54.501 --> 00:29:56.753
Will you? Even now. posthumously?

447
00:30:00.089 --> 00:30:03.176
I know you did an exclusive
with <i>The New York Examiner.</i>

448
00:30:03.259 --> 00:30:06.596
but I'm guessing that's only
going to scratch the surface.

449
00:30:07.680 --> 00:30:09.015
I bet you have more to say

450
00:30:10.016 --> 00:30:11.856
- about the state of your marriage...
- Miss...

451
00:30:12.101 --> 00:30:13.186
Cruz. is it?

452
00:30:13.394 --> 00:30:15.021
I don't know if anyone's told you.

453
00:30:15.104 --> 00:30:17.184
but when the president visits
this part of the plane.

454
00:30:17.232 --> 00:30:18.792
it's usually considered off the record.

455
00:30:19.692 --> 00:30:21.462
But you can ask my press secretary
anything you like

456
00:30:21.486 --> 00:30:22.686
once we're back on the ground.

457
00:30:33.581 --> 00:30:35.500
You're especially quiet this evening.

458
00:30:37.126 --> 00:30:38.711
Maybe I'm a little agitated.

459
00:30:43.591 --> 00:30:46.845
Our patients don't do too well
when it comes to fireworks.

460
00:30:46.928 --> 00:30:48.847
Ah. Pardon me.

461
00:30:56.145 --> 00:30:57.145
Yes?

462
00:30:57.480 --> 00:31:00.108
I don't understand why you leave that on
when we're meeting.

463
00:31:00.817 --> 00:31:04.237
Well. it's not like you're saying
anything different or new.

464
00:31:04.696 --> 00:31:07.115
Your dedication to your script
would be admirable

465
00:31:07.198 --> 00:31:09.033
if it weren't so concerning.

466
00:31:12.412 --> 00:31:14.664
In a few weeks.
I'll be appearing at a hearing

467
00:31:15.123 --> 00:31:17.166
regarding your state of mind

468
00:31:18.251 --> 00:31:20.253
and when it comes to your confession.

469
00:31:20.753 --> 00:31:23.715
even a guilty man
changes his story now and then.

470
00:31:27.886 --> 00:31:29.220
Who do you answer to?

471
00:31:30.597 --> 00:31:32.015
I mean. who do you work for?

472
00:31:33.683 --> 00:31:35.310
You.

473
00:31:37.145 --> 00:31:38.855
That's the idea. anyway.

474
00:31:40.398 --> 00:31:42.191
Everybody works for somebody.

475
00:31:48.573 --> 00:31:50.950
I worked for a man who refused to fail.

476
00:31:53.202 --> 00:31:54.662
I respected that.

477
00:31:55.830 --> 00:31:57.206
I appreciated it.

478
00:32:02.795 --> 00:32:04.130
I'd be dead without him.

479
00:32:05.131 --> 00:32:06.131
Why?

480
00:32:17.393 --> 00:32:20.563
I was working as an aide
for a congressman.

481
00:32:21.356 --> 00:32:23.191
He was idealistic and naive.

482
00:32:23.650 --> 00:32:25.568
Had one-term written all over him.

483
00:32:27.236 --> 00:32:30.615
But I needed a job. a place to be.

484
00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:33.952
I was barely keeping it together.

485
00:32:37.956 --> 00:32:40.041
Francis and I met at some function.

486
00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:42.669
You know. the kind you stand up at.

487
00:32:46.506 --> 00:32:49.884
I don't know how he knew.
but I had eight bottles in my trunk.

488
00:32:51.052 --> 00:32:53.172
I got through four that night
when he came to my door.

489
00:32:55.682 --> 00:32:57.016
I don't remember much.

490
00:32:58.184 --> 00:32:59.352
Not clearly.

491
00:33:03.147 --> 00:33:04.399
He took me to his home.

492
00:33:06.192 --> 00:33:07.360
But Claire...

493
00:33:11.155 --> 00:33:12.615
Francis got me dry.

494
00:33:14.951 --> 00:33:17.412
I shook so badly
I thought I was gonna die.

495
00:33:20.123 --> 00:33:22.041
And then when I was finally got clean.

496
00:33:23.084 --> 00:33:24.752
he gave me my first job.

497
00:33:27.088 --> 00:33:28.131
As an aide?

498
00:33:30.133 --> 00:33:31.718
Hmm. Sort of.

499
00:33:33.386 --> 00:33:36.180
He asked me to go talk
to Congressman Kyle from Iowa.

500
00:33:36.973 --> 00:33:37.973
To what end?

501
00:33:40.018 --> 00:33:41.269
To persuade him.

502
00:33:44.105 --> 00:33:45.273
And I did.

503
00:33:51.404 --> 00:33:52.488
But Claire...

504
00:33:54.365 --> 00:33:55.950
The way she treated him.

505
00:33:58.369 --> 00:33:59.871
in life and in death...

506
00:34:08.588 --> 00:34:11.132
But you pay a price.
when you work for somebody like him.

507
00:34:12.216 --> 00:34:13.426
Somebody you owe.

508
00:34:22.310 --> 00:34:24.604
Somebody close to me died
in a car accident.

509
00:34:28.149 --> 00:34:30.234
That's how I broke the terms
of my house arrest.

510
00:34:33.488 --> 00:34:35.198
I went to see the site of her wreck.

511
00:34:37.075 --> 00:34:39.160
It was twisted on the side of the road.

512
00:34:43.372 --> 00:34:44.749
I just stood there.

513
00:34:46.459 --> 00:34:47.585
An accident?

514
00:34:50.588 --> 00:34:51.839
So they said.

515
00:34:54.550 --> 00:34:55.927
And Zoe Barnes?

516
00:34:59.263 --> 00:35:00.348
I killed her.

517
00:35:02.433 --> 00:35:03.726
For the president.

518
00:35:14.862 --> 00:35:16.572
That's what he used to do when he won.

519
00:35:20.409 --> 00:35:23.204
What did he leave you with?

520
00:35:30.920 --> 00:35:35.299
Last thing that Francis gave me
was the letter opener from his desk.

521
00:35:37.343 --> 00:35:38.845
I mean. I chose it. but...

522
00:35:42.974 --> 00:35:45.935
But I guess really the last thing
he gave me was an apology.

523
00:35:48.229 --> 00:35:50.106
I spoke to him the night he died.

524
00:37:22.740 --> 00:37:25.243
<i>My presidency will not rest.</i>

525
00:37:25.910 --> 00:37:29.705
<i>Nancy has been an inspiration to me.
A tireless warrior.</i>

526
00:37:29.789 --> 00:37:33.542
<i>I promise her and all of you
that I will work on behalf of the rights</i>

527
00:37:33.626 --> 00:37:37.672
<i>and freedoms earned
over the last 241 years of our democracy.</i>

528
00:37:38.547 --> 00:37:40.299
<i>Tyrants come in many forms...</i>

529
00:37:40.383 --> 00:37:41.259
Pathetic.

530
00:37:41.342 --> 00:37:44.011
<i>From the American oligarchs trying
to change the very...</i>

531
00:37:52.895 --> 00:37:55.898
Are you sure you don't want
to take an hour or two to...

532
00:37:55.982 --> 00:37:58.359
Mark. I'm inside the White House.

533
00:37:58.442 --> 00:38:00.945
There's only two of us in the Oval.
so unless you're packing.

534
00:38:01.028 --> 00:38:04.490
- it's literally the safest place I can be.
- Well. I'm not packing. Madam President.

535
00:38:04.573 --> 00:38:07.702
but no one would fault you
for taking a breath for a minute.

536
00:38:09.495 --> 00:38:10.955
I'm breathing just fine.

537
00:38:12.248 --> 00:38:14.208
Can we keep news of this contained?

538
00:38:14.917 --> 00:38:17.753
- I've taken every possible step. I think.
- So who is he?

539
00:38:19.213 --> 00:38:22.258
Well. they did forensics on the route.

540
00:38:22.341 --> 00:38:24.552
Compared notes with the aerial detail.

541
00:38:25.428 --> 00:38:28.055
Homeland Secretary and the Bureau
were brought in.

542
00:38:28.848 --> 00:38:32.101
He never left the place
he took the shot from.

543
00:38:37.648 --> 00:38:40.568
Can you answer a single question directly
and simply?

544
00:38:43.362 --> 00:38:47.992
He shot himself in the head
with his own US military-issued handgun.

545
00:38:50.202 --> 00:38:51.620
And we're sure he's the one?

546
00:38:51.704 --> 00:38:53.789
Yeah. Pro-militia. Anti-government.

547
00:38:54.498 --> 00:38:57.209
Dishonorably discharged last year.
All the typical markers.

548
00:38:57.293 --> 00:38:59.045
Secret Service is confident.

549
00:38:59.503 --> 00:39:01.088
And the Bureau's investigating.

550
00:39:04.383 --> 00:39:07.011
How did Bill Shepherd get his hands
on my speech?

551
00:39:08.429 --> 00:39:09.680
What? Um...

552
00:39:09.805 --> 00:39:12.975
Well. the press usually gets it
hours before.

553
00:39:13.059 --> 00:39:15.269
It wouldn't be that hard
to access a copy. I guess.

554
00:39:18.731 --> 00:39:20.274
I won't be signing that today.

555
00:39:25.446 --> 00:39:28.324
You went there to declare
your independence. and you declared war.

556
00:39:28.407 --> 00:39:29.325
That was a mistake.

557
00:39:29.408 --> 00:39:31.303
No. the mistake was I didn't hire
a chief of staff.

558
00:39:31.327 --> 00:39:33.007
and things are slipping
through the cracks.

559
00:39:33.079 --> 00:39:36.079
That's where I have to disagree with you.
We need to keep this circle small.

560
00:39:37.208 --> 00:39:39.460
You know. Francis warned me about you.

561
00:39:44.006 --> 00:39:46.801
I assure you. I serve at your pleasure.
Madam President.

562
00:39:47.301 --> 00:39:50.179
You need to stop meeting in my office
without me.

563
00:39:54.016 --> 00:39:55.016
Yes. ma'am.

564
00:40:03.943 --> 00:40:06.704
Secret Service took the lead.
But do you believe the theory?

565
00:40:07.780 --> 00:40:11.534
That it was a disgruntled service person
who took a shot at me?

566
00:40:11.784 --> 00:40:12.952
PID does.

567
00:40:14.662 --> 00:40:16.163
I'm asking what you think.

568
00:40:18.541 --> 00:40:23.129
It depends if it was a warning
or an actual attempt.

569
00:40:24.255 --> 00:40:27.842
Given the accuracy. the shooter
would have been informed enough to know

570
00:40:27.925 --> 00:40:30.803
that a .50 caliber round
wouldn't penetrate the Beast.

571
00:40:32.346 --> 00:40:33.681
I think he wanted to scare you.

572
00:40:34.306 --> 00:40:35.766
On behalf of someone.

573
00:40:35.850 --> 00:40:38.394
Lots of people make threats
against sitting presidents.

574
00:40:38.477 --> 00:40:41.188
I'm starting to believe
Francis was murdered.

575
00:40:46.026 --> 00:40:49.738
Before he died. he aligned himself
with some very powerful people.

576
00:40:49.822 --> 00:40:51.883
And I think they turned on him.
and they wanted him dead.

577
00:40:51.907 --> 00:40:53.784
and I think they want me dead. too.

578
00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:57.788
Do you think that sounds crazy?

579
00:40:59.915 --> 00:41:00.916
No. ma'am.

580
00:41:01.709 --> 00:41:04.128
But I think we need to bring in
Special Agent Bowman...

581
00:41:04.211 --> 00:41:06.505
Of these people. these powerful families.

582
00:41:06.589 --> 00:41:10.050
they advocate
dismantling intelligence agencies.

583
00:41:10.301 --> 00:41:12.303
CIA. FBI. Homeland.

584
00:41:12.553 --> 00:41:13.553
You know that. right?

585
00:41:13.596 --> 00:41:15.347
- Ma'am...
- We cannot bring

586
00:41:15.431 --> 00:41:17.475
anyone else in at the moment.

587
00:41:19.143 --> 00:41:20.686
I'm relying on you

588
00:41:21.520 --> 00:41:23.397
the way I know my husband could.

589
00:41:24.023 --> 00:41:25.941
So. please see what you can find.

590
00:41:33.574 --> 00:41:34.825
Is it ever Nate

591
00:41:35.242 --> 00:41:36.410
or always Nathan?

592
00:41:38.120 --> 00:41:39.120
Nathan.

593
00:41:40.956 --> 00:41:41.999
Like Francis.

594
00:41:42.458 --> 00:41:43.542
For me. anyway.

595
00:41:48.797 --> 00:41:51.383
Oh. have you spoken to Doug Stamper?

596
00:41:54.428 --> 00:41:55.428
No.

597
00:41:57.348 --> 00:41:58.682
I'm so worried about him.

598
00:41:58.766 --> 00:42:02.645
He did things no one
in this White House should be proud of.

599
00:42:26.627 --> 00:42:27.627
Hey. Mom.

600
00:42:27.836 --> 00:42:29.713
<i>How many people do you have there?</i>

601
00:42:29.797 --> 00:42:31.006
Not many.

602
00:42:31.298 --> 00:42:33.175
Nobody that interesting. anyway.

603
00:42:34.468 --> 00:42:35.844
Her visit to the base.

604
00:42:36.387 --> 00:42:37.429
Independence speech.

605
00:42:37.513 --> 00:42:39.890
<i>even the naughty soldier
is playing well for her.</i>

606
00:42:39.974 --> 00:42:42.434
Her charmed life persists.

607
00:42:43.060 --> 00:42:44.937
<i>Tell Uncle Bill we should step up.</i>

608
00:42:45.020 --> 00:42:47.856
I can manage the narrative. De-charm her.

609
00:42:47.940 --> 00:42:49.316
<i>He won't like that.</i>

610
00:42:49.400 --> 00:42:51.777
He's not going to like any of it.
so what's the difference?

611
00:42:52.778 --> 00:42:55.948
- I don't know.
- Mom. just say the word.

612
00:42:58.242 --> 00:42:59.242
Trust me.

613
00:42:59.535 --> 00:43:02.246
Don't do a thing
until I get back to you.

614
00:43:22.725 --> 00:43:24.852
Can't even tell you're still in DC.

615
00:43:25.519 --> 00:43:28.522
There are parts of this city
that will always remain a secret.

616
00:43:33.444 --> 00:43:34.804
I don't think I'll be welcome back

617
00:43:34.862 --> 00:43:37.615
in the White House press pool
anytime soon. FYI.

618
00:43:38.324 --> 00:43:39.366
Doesn't matter.

619
00:43:41.535 --> 00:43:42.995
She won't speak to me.

620
00:43:43.078 --> 00:43:45.873
- An interview? Not after...
- She will.

621
00:43:54.590 --> 00:43:56.967
<i>Tonight. for the first time.
he was forthcoming.</i>

622
00:43:57.051 --> 00:43:58.802
But still saying he's guilty?

623
00:43:58.886 --> 00:44:00.346
<i>Yeah. as always.</i>

624
00:44:01.430 --> 00:44:03.932
And did he mention Mr. Grayson by name?

625
00:44:04.016 --> 00:44:06.685
<i>No. He was just more distressed.</i>

626
00:44:07.353 --> 00:44:08.646
So he's getting worse?

627
00:44:08.729 --> 00:44:10.606
<i>Or better. he's finally talking.</i>

628
00:44:12.816 --> 00:44:16.111
But the idea of his leaving the facility
anytime soon.

629
00:44:16.737 --> 00:44:20.074
that's still out of the question.
I mean. for his own good.

630
00:44:20.282 --> 00:44:21.867
<i>He's either guilty of the crime</i>

631
00:44:21.950 --> 00:44:24.078
<i>- or psychotic for admitting to it.</i>
- Madam President.

632
00:44:24.703 --> 00:44:26.343
Miss Shepherd is on the White House line.

633
00:44:29.291 --> 00:44:32.169
Well. maybe it's time to give him
one of the antipsychotics.

634
00:44:32.586 --> 00:44:36.006
Possibly. But we'd have to consider
his history of addiction.

635
00:44:37.174 --> 00:44:39.218
By the way. in answer to your question.

636
00:44:39.551 --> 00:44:41.178
it was a letter opener.

637
00:44:41.261 --> 00:44:44.056
the last thing that Francis gave him
from his desk.

638
00:44:44.431 --> 00:44:45.891
<i>Keep me posted. Charles.</i>

639
00:44:46.266 --> 00:44:47.393
<i>And thank you.</i>

640
00:44:48.185 --> 00:44:49.185
Sure.

641
00:44:55.567 --> 00:44:57.945
<i>Are you prepared?</i>

642
00:44:59.780 --> 00:45:00.781
Excuse me.

643
00:45:01.490 --> 00:45:04.493
Don't you remember? Andover?

644
00:45:04.576 --> 00:45:05.994
Our prep school joke?

645
00:45:06.078 --> 00:45:10.290
I'm prepared to fail the test.

646
00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:13.127
Are you all right?

647
00:45:16.046 --> 00:45:20.426
I'm sorry to call so late.
I... I heard about what happened today.

648
00:45:23.345 --> 00:45:25.389
<i>These things have a tendency to leak out.</i>

649
00:45:26.348 --> 00:45:27.474
<i>I'm worried about you.</i>

650
00:45:28.267 --> 00:45:30.686
It's bulletproof. the motorcade glass.

651
00:45:30.769 --> 00:45:32.187
<i>Did they catch the guy?</i>

652
00:45:33.439 --> 00:45:35.190
How do you know it's a guy?

653
00:45:36.150 --> 00:45:37.651
It's always a guy. right?

654
00:45:43.240 --> 00:45:47.369
What was it Bill wanted adjusted
in my speech?

655
00:45:50.122 --> 00:45:52.416
<i>Oh. Something about...</i>

656
00:45:53.333 --> 00:45:54.418
<i>freedom.</i>

657
00:45:58.756 --> 00:46:00.424
You're in my thoughts. Claire.

658
00:46:02.217 --> 00:46:03.217
Thank you.

659
00:46:04.136 --> 00:46:06.221
<i>He's still with us. don't you think?</i>

660
00:46:06.305 --> 00:46:07.305
Who? <i>Frank.</i>

661
00:46:09.433 --> 00:46:12.770
<i>We're so glad we got to spend
so much time with him before he died.</i>

662
00:46:15.189 --> 00:46:17.149
He told us some fascinating things.

663
00:46:19.359 --> 00:46:20.652
He's been on my mind.

664
00:46:24.490 --> 00:46:27.326
<i>Bill and I finally went down to Gaffney
a few days ago...</i>

665
00:46:30.120 --> 00:46:31.622
<i>to pay our respects.</i>

666
00:48:20.606 --> 00:48:21.606
Claire!

667
00:48:21.940 --> 00:48:23.358
I shouldn't have let them.

668
00:48:23.442 --> 00:48:24.443
I'm sorry.

669
00:48:25.110 --> 00:48:26.236
Come on out now.

670
00:48:32.034 --> 00:48:33.327
Are you still there?

671
00:48:33.410 --> 00:48:34.410
Yes.

672
00:48:44.421 --> 00:48:45.923
Help!

673
00:48:50.302 --> 00:48:52.137
Help!

674
00:49:08.195 --> 00:49:09.195
I know.

675
00:49:09.446 --> 00:49:11.573
You want to know
what really happened to him.

676
00:49:12.491 --> 00:49:14.743
A man like Francis doesn't just die.

677
00:49:15.452 --> 00:49:16.495
That would be...

678
00:49:17.120 --> 00:49:18.246
what's the word?

679
00:49:19.957 --> 00:49:21.124
"Convenient."
